parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Suspension Failure (Upper Ball Joint Failure)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the upper ball joint can cause the front wheel to collapse, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries.
symptoms: The front wheel folds under the vehicle
the vehicle sways from side to side
loss of control
wheel collapse while parking or driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the stabilizer bar can cause the vehicle to sway from side to side, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle sways from side to side
loss of control
vehicle tips over
vehicle flips over.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS module can cause the vehicle to lose braking functionality, leading to increased stopping distances and potentially resulting in accidents.
symptoms: The ABS warning light illuminates
the vehicle fails to brake properly
the traction control and down hill sensor warning lights illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corroded brake rotors can cause the brake pads to wear unevenly, leading to premature wear and potentially causing the ABS module to fail, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The ABS warning light illuminates
the brake pads wear unevenly
the brake rotors show signs of corrosion.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Head gasket failure can cause engine overheating, leading to damage to other components, engine failure, and potentially leaving the driver stranded or causing an accident.
symptoms: Coolant leakage
engine overheating
temperature gauge rising to high levels
red warning lights on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the coolant pressure connection can cause coolant leakage, leading to engine overheating, damage to other components, and potentially leaving the driver stranded or causing an accident.
symptoms: Coolant leakage
engine overheating
temperature gauge rising to high levels
red warning lights on the dashboard.
